ers does not indicate any\nAbatement of investment confidence in\nthe future. F&ilroad securities are con\nspicuously firm despite the fact that gross\nearnings for tl>e month of May were\n57,250.000 less than expenses, the deficit\nbeing largely due to the \u2022\u2018outlaw\" strike.\nThe Japanese picture brides arriving in\nCalifornia have revived the anti-Jap\nai.sese feeling always latent in the Pacific\nif you want*\nthe genuine\nin bottles\nfor the home\nat soda fountains\nand on draught'\nstates, and there have been some infor\nmal conversations between our govern\nment and that of the Mikado on the\nsubject, but the questions involved, how\never grace they may ultimately become,\ndo not threaten immediate trouble. Im\nmigration from Europe continues to in\ncrease and the arrivals in New York are\nlarge.\nENCOURAGING FOREIGN NEWS\nThe foreign news is nearly all encour\naging. While saying they will never con\nsent the Germans continue to yield to\nthe demands made of them at Spa. Pretty\nmuch all the important questions except\nthe amount of the reparation fund ap\npear to have been settled. Evidence of\nEuropean deflation is still lacking, and\nthe report of the German Reichbank, pub\nlished July 12, shows an increase of 2,300,\n000,000 marks in the note issue for the\npreceding fortnight.\nReflecting European recognition of the\nrapidity wi*h which reconstruction r?\nproceeding abroad, advancing prices and\nmuch speculative activity are reported\non the London stock exchange.\nLower prices for commodities are ap\nparently counted as encouraging in Eng\nland for the Index number of the Lon\ndon Economist fell from 8,199 to 7.S47\nduring the month of June. It Is reported\nthat the British government will assume\nthe unpaid portion of the Anglo-French\nloan, amounting to possibly $150,000.OOflfc^\nand due in the United States next Oc\ntober.\nAn early resumption of British trade\nwith Russia and an armistice between\nPoland and Russia are expected as a re\nsult of negotiations conducted by Lloyd\nGeorge.\nRead in the light of the foregoing rec\nord the Business Barometer continues\nto indicate fair weather here and abroad,\nalthough an area of low pressure may be\nexpected in the United States until\npublic opinion compels those who have\nthe power to relax the artificial tension\nthat has been created in the money mar\nket and put the breath of financial life\nback into the railways by giving them\nliving rates.\nOnly 33.6 per cent of the workers in\nAlabama come under the protection of\nthe compensation law in that state.\nMARION INSTITUTE\nDesignated (>7 War Department, 1920\n\u201cHONOR SCHOOL\u201d\nMarion Institute is noted for the thoroughness of its college and preparatory\ncourses* and is the only military school in this section of the South whose college\n\u2022work is fully accredited by the leading universities. Strangest faculty university\nprofessors.\nThoroughly equipped. Junior and Senior R. O. T. C. Military, educational,\nan oral and physical ideals are merged into a composite spirit of practical character\nftiuilding. Special est Point and Annapolis departments.\nAll branches athletics under experienced coaches. 80-acre campus, modem snd\nconvenient dormitories. 73rd Session begins September 1st, Moderate rates.\nFor catalog and information, address\u2014\nCOL. W. L. MURFEE, President MARION, ALA.\nACADEMY\nLocated right on the Gulf, where gulf breezes and sunshine put the\nhealth glow into the boy and make him alert, active and respon\nsive. Students sleep on screened porches the year round. No other\nplace offers such opportunities for athletics, water sports and study.\nPersonal and classroom association with strong, college-bred faculty\ninsures your boy a rightly trained mind, equipped for life and its\nemergencies, a manly character and a well-controlled will, taught to\ncommand as well as to obey. A teacher to every 20 boys.\nOne parent write*; \"1 am sending you my boy tor\ntwo reasons: One is the tour boys you took from\nthis city; che other is the boy you didn t take.'*\nMilitary and naval training given under Government officers.\nSeparate Junior Department for boys 8 to 15.\ncatmioeus of tke Academy untk {frus\ntration, s Mhownup its outdoor mad school nfo, y+nU\nGulf Coast Military Academy, R. 1, Gulf port, Miss.\nrepresentative will be in this city soon. Watch for announcement.\nSend Us t(Se Sop and W<? will Stef urn You iSeSfan\nWill YOU Profit by the Experience of\nArmour and Company?\nArmour and Company, of Chicago, is\nUsing 150 Dictaphones in its general\noffice. These Dictaphones are especially\nvaluable to the Transportation, Fruit\nPreserving, Reclamation and Advertising\nDepartments. Largo volumes of corre\nspondence can now be handled very\nquickly, for the work is so arranged that a\ndictator f~*n give undivided attention\nto correspondence. There are no delays*\nfor The Dictaphone is always ready\nduring and after office hours.\nWhether your office is large or small,\nphone, wire, or write for a demonstra\ntion today in your office and on your\nwork.\n\u2122E DirTflP/WAE\nRag. V, U Pat. OC a4 flip\n\u201cThe Shortest Route to the Mail-Chute\u201d\nHyatt Roller BearmgCn, Chicago,HI. D.P.Biteher. United State. RdaBly\nOfice Manager, mya: \u201cWe are now wing 34 Baltimore, Mi R. Howard Bland. Viee-Prendent.\nDictaphone. in the oariona departments of ear Chicago mya: \u201cWe hare fonnd tltefThe Dictaphone giraanato\norganization.' The lean In in increaaed lohrae of cor- cleaned production, thereby reducing coat of handling\nreapondenca handled, together arith incraaaed apeed eorreapondence. It tana and praoutea amoancy^ 1\nand a low coat per letter, are gratifying and apeak \u2014two may important factota m the mccaaa ot any i\nfor the efficiency of The Dictaphone.\u201d bnaineaa.\" a\nTHE DICTAPHONE, Phone Main 6729\u2014Call at St^Amer. Trust Bldg.,\nBirmingham\nOfficer alee located ta the following citiaa\nClarkadale. Miaa.\nThere ia h